I"ee<h2 id="learning-goals">Learning Goals</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Recognize the limitations of single role / column-based authorization strategies</li>
  <li>Discuss patterns for implementing more sophisticated authorization strategies</li>
  <li>Practice using ActiveRecord models to implement an authorization strategy from scratch</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="structure">Structure</h2>

<ul>
  <li>15 - Discussion: previously encountered authorization models</li>
  <li>10 - Discussion: a more flexible approach to modeling application roles</li>
  <li>5  - Explore the App</li>
  <li>5  - Break</li>
  <li>25 - Lecture: Creating the models to support the authorization strategy</li>
  <li>5  - Break</li>
